MONGODB GUIDE

MongoDB Overview

MongoDB is a NoSQL document database that stores data in BSON format.

Database
  └── Collection
          └── Document

Example Document:

{
  "_id": "123",
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com"
}

--------------------------------------------------
CRUD OPERATIONS
--------------------------------------------------

Insert One:

db.users.insertOne({
  name: "Mohit",
  age: 26
});

Find All:

db.users.find();

Find One:

db.users.findOne({
  email: "test@gmail.com"
});

Update:

db.users.updateOne(
  { _id: userId },
  {
    $set: {
      name: "Updated Name"
    }
  }
);

Delete:

db.users.deleteOne({
  _id: userId
});

--------------------------------------------------
QUERY OPERATORS
--------------------------------------------------

Greater Than:

{
  age: {
    $gt: 18
  }
}

Less Than:

{
  age: {
    $lt: 60
  }
}

Range Query:

{
  age: {
    $gte: 18,
    $lte: 60
  }
}

Not Equal:

{
  status: {
    $ne: "inactive"
  }
}

--------------------------------------------------
LOGICAL OPERATORS
--------------------------------------------------

AND:

{
  $and: [
    { active: true },
    { age: { $gt: 18 } }
  ]
}

OR:

{
  $or: [
    { role: "admin" },
    { role: "manager" }
  ]
}

--------------------------------------------------
AGGREGATION PIPELINE
--------------------------------------------------

Match:

{
  $match: {
    status: "ACTIVE"
  }
}

Group:

{
  $group: {
    _id: "$department",
    count: {
      $sum: 1
    }
  }
}

Sort:

{
  $sort: {
    createdAt: -1
  }
}

Project:

{
  $project: {
    name: 1,
    email: 1
  }
}

Example:

db.users.aggregate([
  {
    $match: {
      active: true
    }
  },
  {
    $group: {
      _id: "$department",
      total: {
        $sum: 1
      }
    }
  }
]);

--------------------------------------------------
INDEXING
--------------------------------------------------

Create Index:

db.users.createIndex({
  email: 1
});

Compound Index:

db.users.createIndex({
  email: 1,
  status: 1
});

Benefits:
- Faster searching
- Faster sorting
- Better query performance

--------------------------------------------------
MONGOOSE
--------------------------------------------------

Schema:

const UserSchema = new Schema({
  name: String,
  email: String,
  active: Boolean
});

Model:

const User = mongoose.model(
  "User",
  UserSchema
);

Find:

const users = await User.find();

Create:

await User.create({
  name: "Mohit"
});

--------------------------------------------------
BACKUP AND RESTORE
--------------------------------------------------

Backup:

mongodump --db hrms

Restore:

mongorestore --db hrms dump/hrms

--------------------------------------------------
PERFORMANCE TIPS
--------------------------------------------------

- Create indexes for frequently queried fields.
- Use projections to limit returned fields.
- Implement pagination.
- Avoid unnecessary aggregation stages.
- Monitor slow queries.